 (13,'regex','In Notepad++ and VSCode, replace all varied brackets at the beginning of lines in a todo list with a simple hyphen','- in Notepad++ copy in this text
	----------------------
	[x] get money
	[] go to the store
	[..] install software
	[] get books
	[x] check out new book on Amazon
	[..] go to bank
	[] replace all [] with [x] in main todo list
	[] organize shelf
	[] clean desk
	----------------------
- you want to make it look like this:
	----------------------
	-  get money
	-  go to the store
	-  install software
	-  get books
	-  check out new book on Amazon
	-  go to bank
	-  replace all [] with [x] in main todo list
	-  organize shelf
	-  clean desk
	----------------------
- search and replace `\[.*\] ` with `- `
- notice that it also deletes those in the middle of the line, which was not your intention
- and notice that it what it means to be "greedy"
	- if you wanted to take these out as well, then you would have to tell it to be non-greedy: `\[.*?\] `
- but you want to only replace those at the beginning of the line, so do this: `^\[.*\] `
- do the same thing in Visual Studio Code and notice that you can see the selections as you type the regular expression',40,'','2019-04-20 14:58:21','systemUnknown'),
 (14,'regex','Indent blocks of lines below specific lines in a text','- you want to indent each of the lines after lines that start with "TEXT ??"
